From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 22:05:20 +0200
Subject: drm/msm/dp: do not enable the unhandled PLL unlocked interrupt

DP_INTR_PLL_UNLOCKED sits in the DP_INTERRUPT_STATUS1 group, which is
unmasked and routed to the AUX ISR, but nothing consumes it. When the PLL
relocks during link training the bit fires with no AUX transfer in flight
and msm_dp_aux_isr() logs "Unexpected DP AUX IRQ 0x01000000 when not
busy". Drop it from the AUX interrupt group; an interrupt with no handler
should not be enabled.

Signed-off-by: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_ctrl.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_ctrl.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_ctrl.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_ctrl.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_ctrl.c
@@ -41,7 +41,7 @@
 	DP_INTR_WRONG_ADDR | DP_INTR_TIMEOUT | \
 	DP_INTR_NACK_DEFER | DP_INTR_WRONG_DATA_CNT | \
 	DP_INTR_I2C_NACK | DP_INTR_I2C_DEFER | \
-	DP_INTR_PLL_UNLOCKED | DP_INTR_AUX_ERROR)
+	DP_INTR_AUX_ERROR)
 
 #define DP_INTERRUPT_STATUS1_ACK \
 	(DP_INTERRUPT_STATUS1 << DP_INTERRUPT_STATUS_ACK_SHIFT)
-- 
Armbian

